15 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
15
16 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
16
17 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
17
18 the following proposed amendments to Sections 1 and 23 of Article VI
18
19 of the Oklahoma Constitution to read as follows:
19
20 Section 1. A. The Executive authority of the state shall be
20
21 vested in a Governor, Lieutenant Governor, Secretary of State, State
21
22 Auditor and Inspector, Attorney General, State Treasurer,
22
23 Superintendent of Public Instruction, Commissioner of Labor,
23
24 Insurance Commissioner of Insurance, and other officers provided by
24
Req. No. 1468 Page 1
1 law and this Constitution, each of whom shall keep his or her office
1
2 and public records, books, and papers at the seat of government, and
2
3 shall perform such duties as may be designated in this Constitution
3
4 or prescribed by law.
4
5 B. The Secretary of State shall be appointed by the Governor by
5
6 and with the consent of the Senate for a term of four (4) years to
6
7 run concurrently with the term of the Governor.
7
8 C. Upon expiration of the term of the Insurance Commissioner
8
9 elected in 2026, the Insurance Commissioner shall be appointed by
9
10 the Governor by and with the consent of the Senate and shall serve
10
11 at the pleasure of the Governor.
11
12 Section 23. A. There shall be elected by the qualified
12
13 electors of the State, at the first general election, a chief
13
14 officer of the Insurance Department, who shall be styled the
14
15 “Insurance Commissioner”, whose term of office shall be four years:
15
16 Provided, That the first term of the Insurance Commissioner so
16
17 elected, shall expire at the time of the expiration of the term of
17
18 office of the first Governor elected The Insurance Commissioner
18
19 shall be appointed by the Governor by and with the consent of the
19
20 Senate as provided in Section 1 of this article. The Insurance
20
21 Commissioner shall be at least twenty-five (25) years of age and
21
22 well versed in insurance matters.
22
23 B. No person shall be eligible to serve as Insurance
23
24 Commissioner for a period of time in excess of eight (8) years.
24
Req. No. 1468 Page 2
1 Such years need not be consecutive. Any years served by a person
1
2 elected or appointed to serve less than a full term to fill a
2
3 vacancy in such office shall not be included in the limitation set
3
4 forth herein. Any person serving in such position at the time of
4
5 passage of this amendment shall be eligible to complete the term for
